      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis benchmark validation — RH index comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index compared against experimental measurements across 5 operating points. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all points. Mean prediction error 8.3%; maximum error 14.1%. Validation conducted at flow rates 2–6 L/min and rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-piv-velocity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field validation — impeller passage",
      "description": "Particle image velocimetry measurements compared to CFD velocity predictions in the impeller passage region. Velocity magnitude agreement within 12% RMS across the measurement plane. Turbulence intensity predictions within experimental uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-uq-campaign",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "UQ campaign — parametric sensitivity sweep across operating envelope",
      "description": "A structured uncertainty quantification campaign was executed covering inlet flow rate (±15%), blood viscosity (±20%), and rotational speed (±5%). Latin hypercube sampling with 120 CFD evaluations identified worst-case hemolysis conditions. Results confirmed that the nominal operating point represents a conservative bound for RH. Sensitivity rankings: flow rate dominates (Sobol index 0.61), followed by viscosity (0.27) and rotational speed (0.12). The UQ campaign outputs are archived in the validation dataset and referenced in the credibility report narrative; the campaign confirmed model robustness across the intended operating envelope."
    }
  ],
